  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. Specific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but typically involve three key stages:\n\n1. Placement - introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering - conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the money's origin\n3. Integration - reintroducing the \"cleaned\" money into the legitimate economy\n\nSpecific legal elements usually include:\n- Knowingly conducting financial transactions with proceeds from illegal activities\n- Attempting to conceal the source of illegally obtained funds\n- Disguising the nature, location, source, ownership, or control of illegal funds\n\nPenalties can include significant fines and criminal prosecution. Specific details and exact definitions differ between countries and legal systems.",
